				<p class="paragraph--2">Now that things are under control, Lauriat’s team have other projects for the Qualys solution. <b><i>“We plan to extend its use to SOX compliance, by being able to prove a certain level of configuration for certain machines, or even their mere existence. This is where the historical archiving of the analyses will prove very useful. Also, we will consequently be able to place a tag on each asset in order to determine those subject to SOX. This will enable us to be far more precise in the remediation procedure; e.g. we can gain great flexibility in the planning phase when we need to repair an equipment by rebooting, and we known that the machine in question is not within the SOX scope,”</i></b> concludes Guyodo.</p>
